##		- 20260629 JC:
##			- Some edge case bugs fixed.
##			- Added the minor code lines in from the apt version.
##			- Modernized from 39 year-old POSIX, to at least Bash 3.2+ (frozen version for macOS).
##		- 20260327 JC: Better snapshot names. Start with YYYYmmDD-HHMMSS_%z_zfs-auto-snap_*.
##		- 20260629 JC: Bash 3.2+ cleanup pass. FIXED a refactor regression: IFS had lost its tab, which
##			silently broke every multi-dataset and named-dataset run ('for X in $TARGETS' and the
##			'read NAME PROPERTIES' arg check both need tab in IFS). Restored IFS to tab+newline (matches
##			upstream). Adopted 'set -euo pipefail' with the needed guards: do_run captures rc without
##			aborting; logger and the --fast grep are guarded; print_log/do_snapshots return 0. Modernized
##			to [[ ]]/(( )) and typed/lowercase locals. No behaviour change beyond the IFS fix (verified by
##			a dry-run fingerprint and a synthetic prune test).
##		- 20260629 JC: Re-added the two zfsonlinux deltas the refactor had dropped, for 1:1 ancestral parity:
##			--min-size/-m (skip a snapshot when too little is written since the last), and the Darwin
##			GNU-getopt shim. Darwin remains unsupported; the shim is kept only for parity.
##		- 20260629 JC: Dropped %z offset from snapshot names. A '+' offset is invalid in ZFS names, so
##			any UTC/east-of-UTC host would fail. Stamp is now YYYYmmDD-HHMMSS (15 chars); updated the
##			prune glob to match, and simplified the --fast path (leading date sorts without awk).
##		- 20260408 JC:
##			- Fixed potential OG bug where shebang is `#!/bin/sh`, but script has bashisms (e.g. variables defined as 'local').
##			- Changed shebang to #!/bin/bash. There is nothing that calls this script as 'sourced'. The cron scripts use 'exec', which
##			  is not the same as 'source' - the shebang is honored.
##			- Added linting exceptions.
##			- Integrated these changes into a forked project on github.
##		- 20260630 JC:
##			- Added two lines of code from the apt version of zfs-auto-snapshot that had been dropped in the refactor, for 1:1 ancestral parity.
##			- Refactored from POSIX to Bash v3.2+ - for more compactness, readability, debuggability, maintainability, and failure robustness.
##			- Added --min-size/-m option to skip a snapshot when too little is written since the last.
